#eNCA​ Senior reporter Aviwe Mtila was there when humanitarian aid was distributed. #DStv403 KURUMAN - The Gift of the Givers is providing much-needed relief for flood victims in the Northern Cape. The worst flood since 1974 has swept through Kuruman, leaving a trail of destruction and many villagers stranded. READ: Northern Cape premier declares provincial state of disaster Parts of the John Taolo Gaetsewe District have been declared a disaster area.
The villagers are now receiving humanitarian aid.
The Gift of the Givers says there are more trucks, filled with food parcels on its way. Watch the video above for more details on this story.